In England, in the seven days to 27 January, there were 619,958 new confirmed cases (1,096.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 January, there were 629,682 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (9,724 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 01 February is 14,948,735 (26,434.5 cases per 100,000 population).
